column56: Talking with cora was like chatting with a computer programme.

I wasn't sure if Cora understood vegan as a requirement as she offered me fish in the first recipe.
Also healthy doesn't just mean cold salads I was recommend too many salad dishes for winter season.
I think Cora would provide a good service

Well a nice thing that would be good for Cora would be to know if the people are vegetarian, vegan or meat eaters in advance, that would be very easy for people to choose the recipes. A thing that bothered me was the fact that i asked for a recipe for a drink and the only thing that she game me was a food recipe with a drink in the preparation. But in conclusion it was a very good bot and i really enjoyed her. It would be a service that i would look for in the future.
Another thing that could be good as well was to ask for which ingredients people had at home so they don't need to shop to make those recipes.
Good start to the human interaction

column57: I enjoyed this study, thank you!

column56:
I didn't receive any recipe with the ingredients I mentioned (despite not being anything too complicated to cook together, like chicken + carrots + spring onions). I feel like it would be more interesting if Cora had a wider net of recipes available. Also, instead of blindly suggesting recipes, I think it'd be better if you could input the ingredients you have at home into Cora (at least 2-3) as it would help you cook using what you have available in your fridge (instead of having to go out to stock up).
Also, for a chatbot, I feel like reducing the personal/off-topic conversation would help, as there's general expectation that you're chatting with a bot so anything extra feels slightly awkward as it was generated and not genuine.

Other than that, this is a very cool concept that I would definitely use if I found it more useful.
